<title type="html"><![CDATA[Invocations During Ruku (Bowing in Prayer)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=240&amp;p=249#p249"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 150%; line-height: normal"><span style="color: #0000FF">Invocations During Ruku (Bowing in Prayer)</span></span></strong><br /><br />&quot;سُبْحَانَ رَبِّيَ الْعَظِيمِ&quot;.<br /><br />Glory to my Lord the Exalted (three times in Arabic)<br /><br />Reference: Sunan At-Tirmithi and Musnad Ahmad. Graded Sahih by shaykh Al-Albani in Sahih At-Tirmithi 1/83.<br /><br />&quot;سُبْحَانَكَ اللَّهُمَّ رَبَّنَا وَبِحَمْدِكَ اللَّهُمَّ اغْفِرْ لِي&quot;.<br /><br />Glory is to You , O Allah , our Lord , and praise is Yours . O Allah , forgive me.<br /><br />Reference: Al-Bukhari 1/99 andMuslim 1/350.<br /><br />&quot;سُبُّوحٌ، قُدُوسٌ، رَبُّ الْمَلَائِكَةِ وَالرُّوحِ&quot;.<br /><br />Glory (to You) , Most Holy (are You) , Lord of the angels and the Spirit.<br /><br />Reference: Muslim 1/353<br /><br />&quot;اللَّهُمَّ لَكَ رَكَعْتُ، وَبِكَ آمَنْتُ، وَلَكَ أَسْلَمْتُ خَشَعَ لَكَ سَمْعِي، وَبَصَرِي وَمُخِّي، وَعَظْمِي، وَعَصَبِي، وَمَا اسْتَقَلَّ بِهِ قَدَمِي&quot;.<br /><br />O Allah , to You I bow (in prayer) and in You I believe and to You I have submitted. Before You my hearing is humbled , as is my sight , my mind , my bones , my nerves and what my feet have mounted upon (for travel).<br /><br />Reference: Muslim 1/534<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Sat Sep 03, 2016 2:20 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
